::Feline::

Very few things in life had ever really scared her, or came close to 
scaring her.  But HotRod's driving put the fear of the Matrix in 
her.  Her eyes were transfixed on the ground in front of the car.  
She had a white nuckled, death grip on the steering wheel.  She was 
breathing really hard as her spark felt like it would jump right out 
chest.  Her face had the look of sheer terror on it.  She swore under 
her breath that when she finally calmed down, she was going to get 
HotRod back for scaring her out of her skin.
